The paper deals with the problem of designing optimal online-ad investment strategies, which involves game theory (cs.GT) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. The algorithm proposed in the paper is based on a greedy approach, which involves optimization (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the impact of inaccurate estimation of the system dynamics, which falls under the category of statistical learning (cs.SI).
